WEBVTT

00:00:58.588 --> 00:01:00.609
He can multiple three numbers by three numbers

00:01:00.609 --> 00:01:02.396
in his head with ease,

00:01:02.396 --> 00:01:06.154
yet when it comes to trying to have a conversation,

00:01:06.154 --> 00:01:08.215
he has great difficulty.

00:01:08.215 --> 00:01:10.274
He doesn't make eye contact.

00:01:10.274 --> 00:01:12.397
He has difficulty starting a conversation,

00:01:12.397 --> 00:01:14.132
feels awkward,

00:01:14.132 --> 00:01:15.950
and when he gets nervous,

00:01:15.950 --> 00:01:17.675
he actually shuts down.

00:01:17.675 --> 00:01:19.157
Yet both of these boys

00:01:19.157 --> 00:01:23.341
have the same diagnosis of
autism spectrum disorder.

00:01:23.341 --> 00:01:25.769
One of the things that concerns us

00:01:25.769 --> 00:01:27.366
is whether or not there really is

00:01:27.366 --> 00:01:29.339
an epidemic of autism.

00:01:29.339 --> 00:01:31.819
